answer.para:
It happens to me sometimes too. I have this macro to work around it for now:

/** Reset_TextArea.bsh */
view.splitVertically();
view.unsplitCurrent();

					Run this, and jEdit creates
                    a new TextArea for you, and that one won't be confused. This
                    can help avoid the need to restart jEdit. If you can
                    reproduce the steps you took to cause this, please submit a
                    bug report that details what plugins/versions you were
                    using, and how to reproduce it. It may be specific to a file you are editing, or a particular combination of settings you are using, or sequence of actions you performed.
